{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83e2e60e-2afe-415e-8e29-3cf974fbf1ce","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` bundles the runner, framework, and analyzers. No extra package references needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings` or assembly attribute)\n\nAdd an `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel by default.\n\n## 3. Sequential database tests — use `[DoNotParallelize]`\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Insert_CreatesRecord() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Delete_RemovesRecord() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nThe `[DoNotParallelize]` attribute on the class excludes it from parallel execution — those tests run sequentially after all parallel tests complete.\n\n## Summary\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Minimal project file | `MSTest.Sdk` (single SDK reference) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential for DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3b5c5622-a781-48dd-b187-3f51c500e697","outputTokens":397,"requestId":"BD05:1A8D4E:1EA694F:22AEAEC:6A07CEEE"},"id":"9f95ca13-7930-4303-95be-d86c5e315d1b","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:57:10.711Z","parentId":"ff1c8152-70ed-4f86-9885-61e23b7cabce"}
